preview_comments.text: للاسف لم العبها بشكل فعلي فقط مجرد المقدمه .. ولكن لضيق الوقت والتزامي بالعب مع الاصدقاء بالعاب اخرى مثل دستني ٢ .. لم أتمكن حتى الآن من لعبها وهناك العديد من الالعاب التي تستحق التجربه ولكن الوقت فعلا ضيق .. اتمنى ان اجربها واعيش مغامرة سبيدر مان

caption.text: لعبتنا اليوم هي (سيبادر مان) اي بالمعنى الرجل العنكبوت قد نزلت لعبة في آواخر سنة ٢٠١٨ حصرايا على جهاز بلاي استيشن ٤ وقد ترشحت من افضل العاب مغامرة بنفس السنة. قصة لعبة تبدا عندما تسقط اكبر منظمين جرام في مدينة ويقول سوفة تدمر مدينة بسببك ومن هناك تحدث كثير من الامور في مدينة وظهور كثير من مجرمين لم تكن تعرفهم ولا اريد اتكلم عن القصة امثر لانها فعلا قوية ومن نفس كتاب قصص مافل . نظام العبة قد ابدعوا المطورين وقدموا لنا فعلا لعبة سيبادر مان من ناحية قفز من بناية الى اخرى ومن سلسل الى مخبأ الأعداء وحتى أيضا اسلوب القتال فعلا ممتعة وفي كثير من الامور لم استطع اغطيها في تقرير ولكن في خلاصة الأمر أستطيع القول هو لعبة فعلا لا تتطوف بصراحة وانصح فيها بشدة عيبها الوحيد هو حصريا على بلاي استيشن فقط و تستغرق لإنهائها تقريبا ٣٠ ساعة اقيمها ٩/١٠

Melalui trailer terbarunya, Respawn Entertainment tunjukkan Season 3 Apex Legends bertajuk “Meltdown” dalam sebuah gameplay. Seperti yang bisa kamu lihat di atas, kita akan dapatkan beberapa hal baru untuk update dari season 3 ini. Yang pertama dengan munculnya legend baru yaitu Crypto, map baru yang bernama World’s End yang didalamnya ada kereta api, geyser, lapisan berlava, hingga dinginnya salju yang akan menjadi satu di map. Dan Charged Rifle yang juga sempat muncul di Titanfall. Senjata ini sepertinya akan menjadi momok yang berbahaya saat ditembakkan ke legends lain. Charged Rifle bisa one-shot kill semua musuhmu. Senjata ini hanya akan muncul sebagai senjata drop yang datang secara acak. Season ketiga Meltdown diirilis di Apex Legends pada tanggal 1 Oktober 2019 ini! Buruan mainkan sekarang!

(45b) Corporal Vale stands at attention as Lucian approaches, “My lord.” Lucian, “I’m sorry?” Vale, “How may I help you my lord?” Lucian try not to look dumbfounded, "I...I don’t have time to run up to the Outskirt camp. Do you have extra arms and armor in your supply chest?” Vale, “Yes. Are you and the heralds leaving?” Lucian, “Soon, beginning from the West Road. With every area cleared, we will plant a marker.” Vale, “Yes sir.” Lucian, "Thank you..corporal sir." He anxiously turns on his heel and scurries off into one of the tents. A moment later ---- “A minor adjustment? This is not the time to try something new.” Cassandra blares. Lucian, “You didn’t give me a chance to tell you what I’m good at before you cloaked me in armor and daggers.” Cassandra, “You said you’re a proficient hunter.” Lucian, “Not at close range.” Cassandra, “Fine. Now that you’re well suited for the journey, I need you to survey ahead but don’t engage with the enemy until we do.” Lucian, “The mages are out of control but who wouldn't be in confinement.” Cassandra, “So you sympathesize with them?" Lucian "I can relate." Cassandra "And the templars?” Lucian laments, “I have searched my feelings since I arrived at Haven. I can’t forgive those who have taken what little I had but I am more open to accepting that there are those like Commander Cullen or Sir Trevelyan.” Cassandra, “Oh? What do you sense in Abram?” Lucian, “Do you know that male nugs are the ones who raises the babies alone in burrows for months? An accidental step near their burrow might cost you a limb." Cassandra, “Tbey seem so skittish and timid.” Lucian, “Well, that is Lord Abram Trevelyan.” Cassandra, “Huh. Leliana will be fascinated to learn of that.” Lucian, “Does she fancy him?” Cassandra, “No. She has a thing for nugs.” Together, they rush up the stone path where the group awaits at the mouth of the tunnel leading into the West Road. #dragonage #da #dai #trevelyan 
#dragonageinquisition #inquisition #games #gaming #gamer #gamers #gaymer #bioware #biowaregames #videogame #videogames

(45) “What’s wrong?” Abram snaps out of his rumination to turn to Cassandra who’s been intensely eyeing him. “What do you mean?” Cassandra, “Is it something that the villager said?” Abram shakes his head, “All he said is that we need to reach his son for a potion that will relieve his wife’s illness.” Cassandra, “Will it require grounded fungus and skeletal remains infused with demonic essence?” Abram scoffs, “The potion is suppose to help her breath, not infect her.” Cassandra, “Then why are you standing there looking so grave?” Abram ease the tension on his face to give a half-hearted grin, “I was thinking about.…about my parents.” Cassandra, “I can have Harding send a missive to Haven to see if Leliana received word from Ostwick.” Abram, “Thank you but not necessary.” Cassandra, “If that will give you a peace of mind to focus on…” Abram interrupts, “Any more news on the horse master?” Cassandra, “The farm remained unscathed from the fighting but I don’t know for how long. Give me a moment to talk to Harding…” Abram cuts her off, “Clearing the West Road will help our soldiers gain a foothold of the crossing. We must do so now.” Cassandra resigns with a sigh, “Yes, we should go.” At the corner of her eye, she sees Lucian walking by. Cassandra, “Scout Durand!” Lucian jogs up to Cassandra and bows, “Seeker.” Cassandra, “Gather the others. We’re heading to the West Road. You should also prepare.” Lucian speaks without looking up, “Understood. I just need to make a minor adjustment to my provision.” Cassandra, “Do what you must but do it quick.” “Yes ser.” Without a pause, Lucian dashes off. Abram trails Lucian with his eyes, “He seems a little nervous.” Cassandra, “I have faith that he will do well. I believe your siblings have been speaking with Scout Whittle by the entrance. I will join you there.” #dragonage #dragonageinquisition #da #dai #inquisitor #templar #bioware #biowaregames #games #videogame #videogames #gaming #gamer #gaymer

Recently picked up the vinyl soundtrack for Red Dead Redemption 2.
.
I'm not usually a buyer of vinyls but I went with the Ultimate Edition of the game with the collectors box so thought I'd go and get the limited edition soundtrack to go with it.
.
It's a fantastic game that I'm still playing. I have finished the main story but there are so many other side missions and challenges I've still not hit 90% complete.
.
Did anyone else get the vinyl soundtrack?
.

caption.text:
My first impressions of the N-Switch game controller from Ipega are surprisingly positive. I was interested in it because it was a mix of third party joycons, which I mainly wanted for better chances with the controls sticks, and a Switch grip that would not only make handheld mode more comfortable but also offer more support to the connection points on the side when holding it.
.
I played Yooka-Laylee for a few hours with it tonight and despite it not having a full back like I thought it did, it still is surprisingly supportive yet lightweight. The layout is a tad awkward but I adjusted to it fine and the feel is decent. The buttons definitely feel strange and the d-pad is a little stiff, but the sticks are actually pretty nice, especially with those concave tops to keep your thumbs in place.
.
A few things to note are that there's no NFC compatibility, no rumble, no motion controls, and to get this working you have to first turn wired pro controller connection on in the setting with a different controller, THEN slide the Switch into place, and don't try updating the controller or it will go out of sync after failing. So it basically just feeds off the battery of the Switch for power, but it didn't seem to hog much power compared to playing with other controllers as far as I've noticed.
.
You'll see the Wii U gamepad here not only for a size comparison but also a reminder. The Switch can be used not just as a console, a handheld, or a portable console via tabletop mode. It can also be used for off TV play! It's a pretty limited concept, sure, but if you just want to watch something on your TV while you play then it's great to have around the house. It's not going to be a great travel companion due to its size and awkward shape, and while on the TV you might as well use a pro controller, but just playing off your TV at home... this thing is pretty nice.
.
One word of warning: Your Switch might be a little tough to get out of this thing. That's nice to know it won't come falling out, even if you tip it upside down, but it can be a little scary prying it out of there. I'm hoping worst case scenario will be that the accessory breaks.
.
Thoughts on this... thing?

TRUE 😍
.
.
.
.
.
.
